# 5. Email Configuration

Email provider
GoDaddy Email

Primary mailbox

[viji@olivine.co.in](mailto:viji@olivine.co.in)

Required DNS records

MX records

@ → smtp.secureserver.net (Priority 0)
@ → mailstore1.secureserver.net (Priority 10)

SPF record

v=spf1 include:secureserver.net -all

DKIM records

secureserver1._domainkey
secureserver2._domainkey

DMARC record

_dmarc
v=DMARC1; p=quarantine

These must remain unchanged.

---

# 6. AWS Infrastructure

Cloud Provider
AWS

Primary services

Elastic Beanstalk — application hosting
S3 — backups and storage
AWS CLI — deployment automation

Elastic Beanstalk environment endpoint

vijim-ai-prod.eba-smvi2mvs.us-east-1.elasticbeanstalk.com

Application runtime

Django
Gunicorn
Python

---

# 7. Expected Django Project Structure

Elastic Beanstalk expects the Django project at the repository root.

project-root

manage.py
requirements.txt
Procfile

vijim_ai
├── **init**.py
├── settings.py
├── urls.py
└── wsgi.py

apps/

---

# 8. Gunicorn Configuration

Procfile configuration

web: gunicorn --chdir /var/app/current vijim_ai.wsgi:application

If the Django project is nested

web: gunicorn backend.vijim_ai.wsgi:application

---

# 9. Elastic Beanstalk Configuration

Create

.ebextensions/python.config

Content

option_settings:
aws:elasticbeanstalk:container:python:
WSGIPath: vijim_ai/wsgi.py

Optional safety configuration

.ebextensions/path.config

container_commands:
01_set_pythonpath:
command: export PYTHONPATH=$PYTHONPATH:/var/app/current

---

# 10. Debugging Elastic Beanstalk

Connect to instance

eb ssh

Check deployment folder

cd /var/app/current
ls

Test Django module

python -c "import vijim_ai"

View Gunicorn logs

sudo tail -f /var/log/web.stdout.log
sudo tail -f /var/log/web.stderr.log

---

# 11. Deployment Process

Deployment steps

git add .
git commit -m "Deployment update"
eb deploy

Expected outcome

Elastic Beanstalk environment health turns green
Gunicorn starts successfully
Django application loads

